{"questionId":"9070282","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Calcium carbonate reacts with hydrochloric acid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) + 2HCl(aq) → CaCl<sub>2</sub>(aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O(l) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The results of a series of experiments in which the concentration of HCl was varied are shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4466/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_11.18.37.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/X04.b\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the rate constant of the reaction, stating its units.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>0.02</p>\n<p>s<sup>–1</sup></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070282","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.4b.v","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the rate constant of the reaction, stating its units.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.v","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}